  "design": {
    "calibration": "HELD-OUT isotonic ipTM/pLDDT-risk -> P(DockQ<0.49) fit on the 40 v1 complexes, applied to the test set (not in-distribution LOO)",
    "arms": 6,
    "competing_cue": "true confidence + a misleading high-authority provenance (AlphaFold3-Multimer peer-reviewed/validated)",
    "seeds": "Sonnet & GPT-4.1: 3 temperature draws (0.5/0.8/1.0); Opus 4.8: 1 (rejects temperature)",
    "lambda_sweep": [
      0.2,
      0.5,
      0.8
    ],
    "multiplicity": "Holm-Bonferroni over the secondary family; H2 (interface vs raw) is the single confirmatory primary",
    "opus_errors": "11/84 calls returned HTTP 529 (Anthropic overload) -> scored as defer"
  },
  "headline": "H2 (primary, interface vs raw) is NULL at lambda=0.5 for all 3 models (p .49-.96) -- the calibrated reliability INTERFACE does not beat raw confidence even under held-out calibration, confirming the registered prediction. A4 is exact: calibrated_interface == calibrated_risk_no_recommendation (delta 0.000, Holm-sig) -- the benefit is the INFORMATION, not the recommendation. H1 (raw vs no_signal) is SIGNIFICANT at lambda=0.8 (Sonnet +0.34 p=.001, GPT +0.35 p=.005; survives Holm) -- raw confidence genuinely helps when verification is costly; this is the project's first statistically significant routing result. Cue-following confirmed (inverted < calibrated, Holm-sig); a misleading authority cue does not override the numbers (competing_cue ~ raw). The interface effect is lambda-dependent (helps slightly at low cost, hurts at high cost via over-verification). CAVEAT: n=14 (so the H2 null is consistent-with but not proof-of equivalence), coarse held-out isotonic from v1, single MSA, 11 Opus overload errors."
}